Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt:
9:00 AM /Room 301/ Defendant Ofelia Julio Diaz in court.  Attorney Wright C. Laufenberg in court for Ofelia Julio Diaz.  Attorney Kelly L Hays in court for State of Wisconsin. Interpreter Susan Rascon in court. Interpreter is sworn in. Defendant waives right to preliminary hearing. Remarks by defendant's atty. Letters were given to court. Remarks by court. Court advises defendant of benefits and risks of preliminary hearing. Defendant waives right to preliminary hearing. Court finds defendant has waived right to preliminary hearing. Court finds probable cause. Court binds over case. State has filed information and emailed copy to defense. Defendant's atty has received copy of information. Remarks by defendant's atty. Defendant pleads not guilty. Court receives defendant's pleas of not guilty. Court gives remarks. State has complied with victim's rights. December 5th @11:00 status conference. Court advises if case can be resolved with an agreement, to let court know as soon as possible. Court advises defendant must keep address and phone current with atty and coc. Court advises defendant to communicate with atty.
Status conference scheduled for December 5, 2022 at 11:00 am.

09:01 AM in Room 301. Defendant Ofelia Julio Diaz in court with attorney Wright C. Laufenberg.  Kelly L Hays appeared for the State of Wisconsin. Susan Rascon duly sworn as interpreter. Attny Laufenberg acknowledges receipt of complaint, waives reading, requesting preliminary hearing but wiling to waive timelines; has discussed with Def. right to P.H. in 20 days. Def. agrees with attorney's summation. Off the record for scheduling. On the record. Court accepts Def. waiver of time limits for P.H.  Preliminary hearing scheduled for September 7, 2022 at 09:00 am.

02:24 PM. Defendant Ofelia Julio Diaz in court, in custody.  Kelly L Hays appeared for the State of Wisconsin.  Ofelia Julio Diaz appeared by video means. All parties via zoom.  John Vaughn, Interpreter, duly sworn under oath.   Def. has copy of complaint, advised of charges and penalties.  Def. given atty rights and given 3 options, PD, hire own or court appointed atty. Def. want a court appointed atty.  Court advise def. needs to apply for PD first and if denied than may apply for court appointed atty. State gives bail/bond recommendation. Def. heard on bond.  Court orders $2,000 cash bond with condition. Court gives concern RE: new date and going to set for two dates, one to check on status of atty & to make sure bond is posted and other date when court has an interpreter scheduled.  Adjourned initial appearance scheduled for June 1, 2022 at 09:00 am.  Status conference scheduled for April 4, 2022 at 11:00 am.
